WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.670
Based on and inspired by the teachings
of Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, this series

00:00:02.670 --> 00:00:05.574
aims to explore the evolutionary relationship
between two interconnected domains

00:00:05.574 --> 00:00:07.844
expressing human awareness
at the gross and subtle levels.

00:00:07.844 --> 00:00:11.115
It endeavors to elucidate this complex interplay
between the current scientific understanding

00:00:11.115 --> 00:00:13.919
of human neuroanatomy; the autonomic
nervous system in particular,

00:00:13.919 --> 00:00:16.923
and the so-called subtle system as described
in the traditional literature on yoga.

00:00:16.923 --> 00:00:19.961
Ultimately, the series tries to bring its viewers
along this exploratory journey

00:00:19.961 --> 00:00:23.500
to experience these relationships through meditation
as taught by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi.

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:54.960
Science and Spirituality.

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:56.880
The debate goes on.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:01.360
But really, scientists and spiritualists
are both seeking the answers

00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:04.480
to the same question
just in different ways.

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:07.520
They both try to find
the hidden laws of nature,

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:09.840
the higher power
that created everything,

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:13.440
and use their discoveries
to better the life of others.

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:17.200
And with this interview series,
we have tried to learn more

00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:21.680
about the intersection of science
and spirituality with our guest,

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:26.000
who is very unique in being both
a neurologist and a long-standing

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.920
meditation practitioner.

00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:30.480
So what better way
than to talk to him

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:31.920
and find out more?

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:34.080
I would like to welcome
Dr. Ashish Prathan

00:01:34.080 --> 00:01:35.280
on our program today.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:36.800
Welcome, Dr. Ashish.

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:37.760
Thank you.

00:01:37.760 --> 00:01:39.840
Thanks for having me back, Monika.

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:40.640
Definitely.

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:42.480
It's always a pleasure talking to you.

00:01:42.480 --> 00:01:46.240
Dr. Ashish, today we're talking
about the seventh energy center

00:01:46.240 --> 00:01:48.960
in the subtle system,
and we'd like to know

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:51.829
how it is represented
in the human body.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:58.160
The seventh energy center
is the most fascinating,

00:01:58.160 --> 00:02:00.480
obviously the most complex.

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:08.400
And it is very much a symbol,
an anatomical, physiologic symbol

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:11.280
of what spirituality
is really all about,

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:15.280
relative to the introduction
that you just so eloquently made.

00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:17.120
So as we have said
from the very beginning

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:24.160
of this series, adopting
a Cartesian frame of reference,

00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:29.280
where we look at each individual
energy center, although convenient,

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:31.280
is not how the system functions.

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:36.800
We have adopted this modality
because that helps us to understand

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:39.840
at a little more granular level.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:43.600
But the entire system is integrated
right from the first energy center,

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:49.520
right up to the seventh energy center,
which is what we're about to try to answer.

00:02:49.520 --> 00:02:52.480
Within that framework,
given the fact that all

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:56.720
the energy centers are integrated,
the limbic system,

00:02:56.720 --> 00:03:01.920
which is the gross representation
of the seventh energy center,

00:03:01.920 --> 00:03:06.880
is the epitome
of an integral function.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:08.880
So what is the limbic system?

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:13.840
The limbic system is something
that governs our actions

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:15.760
and our behaviors.

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:21.200
It is, one might say,
one of the most primitive forms

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.320
of neurological systems
within the body.

00:03:24.320 --> 00:03:28.080
So if you think about it,
the limbic system sits deep

00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:29.840
inside our brain.

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:33.520
If you think of our brain
as a kind of a coconut,

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:36.560
and if you start going
inside the coconut,

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:43.040
it is literally the core of it all
that comprises the limbic system,

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:47.200
whereas the other layers
start developing outwardly.

00:03:47.200 --> 00:03:50.560
And if you look at the evolution
of how this has come about,

00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:56.240
you find the correspondences
of the limbic system

00:03:56.240 --> 00:04:00.480
as you go downward -
if we consider

00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:04.080
the primate neurological systems

00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:07.280
of which the Homo sapiens
is a part, that is us,

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:10.480
as you go downwards
on the evolutionary scale,

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:14.480
you can find there are aspects
of the so-called limbic system.

00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:18.880
So the limbic system in a way
might be referred to as a kind

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:21.600
of a primitive brain,
but it is anything but primitive.

00:04:21.600 --> 00:04:27.360
And the reason is, it comprises
multiple organs within the brain

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.040
or parts of the brain.

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:33.200
To call it an organ
is probably a misnomer.

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:37.520
And we will talk about two or three
of these,

00:04:37.520 --> 00:04:41.520
but that probably might be
the next question.

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:43.040
But that is what it is.

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:48.560
The limbic system is situated
deep inside our brain,

00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:52.640
and it corresponds
to the seventh energy center,

00:04:52.640 --> 00:05:00.240
and it serves as a kind
of a major integrative aspect

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:06.240
of the sensory inputs
and the motor responses

00:05:08.480 --> 00:05:10.560
that the body provides.

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:15.920
So you just mentioned
different parts of the limbic system.

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:18.960
Could you just elaborate
a little bit more about that?

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:20.000
Sure, happy to.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:26.560
In the last episode,
we spoke about the hypothalamus,

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:30.000
which is related
to the sixth energy center.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.640
But as we said
just a few moments ago

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:34.800
that the whole thing is integrated.

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:39.440
There are two or three other parts
of the limbic system

00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:41.840
that I would briefly
like to touch upon.

00:05:41.840 --> 00:05:44.480
The first one would be the amygdala.

00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:48.080
The amygdala, we have two
amygdalas so to speak,

00:05:48.080 --> 00:05:51.680
one in the left brain, another one
in the right side of the brain.

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:54.160
And these are small
almond-shaped structures,

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.400
a part of the limbic system of course.

00:05:56.400 --> 00:06:01.760
And they relate to our memories
and our emotions.

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:07.120
Say, we see something
that induces fear,

00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:12.720
or fear as a memory
that is engraved in us

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:15.200
is a function of the amygdala.

00:06:15.200 --> 00:06:18.080
So in people who have
a hyperactive amygdala,

00:06:18.080 --> 00:06:20.760
they tend to be more fearful
and so on and so forth.

00:06:20.760 --> 00:06:25.200
Post-Traumatic Stress Disorders,
PTSDs, numerous studies

00:06:25.200 --> 00:06:30.800
that seem to demonstrate a connection
between that kind of a state

00:06:30.800 --> 00:06:33.120
and an overactive amygdala.

00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:36.800
Amygdala is again,
a very important part

00:06:36.800 --> 00:06:40.480
of the limbic system
because it processes our memories,

00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:46.240
it also creates the fear factor,
and so on and so forth.

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:48.480
The other structure
that we would really also

00:06:48.480 --> 00:06:52.080
like to talk about is the hippocampus.

00:06:52.080 --> 00:06:58.720
Hippocampus is what is poetically
described as a seahorse-looking structure

00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:01.600
and it relates to our memories.

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:05.600
Hippocampus plays a very
important role in our spatial memories,

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:08.320
in memories that we form
over a lifetime,

00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:11.760
but also it relates to our time
and place memories,

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:13.760
so that's why spatial memory

00:07:13.760 --> 00:07:17.040
plays a very important role in that.

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:19.440
The third structure I would like
to talk about is the thalamus.

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:24.560
The thalamus, again,
we have two thalami,

00:07:24.560 --> 00:07:27.280
like we have two hippocampi,
there are two of each one of these,

00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:30.640
one on either side of the brain,
but they all sit together.

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:34.560
The thalamus you can think of this
as a massive relay station.

00:07:34.560 --> 00:07:39.280
All these sensory inputs
of heat, cold, whatever,

00:07:39.280 --> 00:07:42.240
the sensations that we feel
in our body,

00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:45.520
they are brought up
through the sensory nerves

00:07:45.520 --> 00:07:48.560
and they then pass
through the thalamus.

00:07:48.560 --> 00:07:53.600
The thalamus you can say is like
a major networking junction

00:07:53.600 --> 00:08:00.000
and from the thalamus,
the nerves then are projected out

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:03.680
into other parts of the brain,
particularly the cerebral cortex

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:06.960
or the temporal lobe,
so on and so forth.

00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:10.000
And then based on that,
responses are created

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:13.360
and they once again
pass through the thalamus.

00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:15.920
So the thalamus acts as

00:08:15.920 --> 00:08:18.720
a relay center
and that's also part

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:21.360
of the limbic system.

00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:23.840
And then we spoke about

00:08:23.840 --> 00:08:25.680
the hypothalamus
in the previous episode,

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:29.665
just briefly the hypothalamus
again is a very important organ,

00:08:29.665 --> 00:08:33.440
very small, very important function
by way of its endocrine functions,

00:08:33.440 --> 00:08:37.280
the way it controls the entirety
of the autonomic nervous system

00:08:37.280 --> 00:08:41.280
by secreting and controlling hormones
that govern our blood pressure,

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:44.400
respiration, digestive system,
so on and so forth.

00:08:44.400 --> 00:08:49.360
Let's integrate it all together
and the pun is very much intended here.

00:08:49.360 --> 00:08:53.692
So through the thalamus,
through the hippocampus,

00:08:53.692 --> 00:08:57.920
through the amygdala,
through the hypothalamus,

00:08:57.920 --> 00:08:59.920
through another part
of the limbic system

00:08:59.920 --> 00:09:03.280
called the anterior cingulate gyrus,
which is also responsible

00:09:03.280 --> 00:09:05.280
for judgmental behaviors.

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:10.000
What you can see is that
the limbic system essentially governs

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:12.480
our vegetative functions.

00:09:12.480 --> 00:09:17.040
It is responsible
for 'the state of being'.

00:09:17.040 --> 00:09:19.600
This is not a spiritual description.

00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:22.320
This is literally
a physiologic description.

00:09:22.320 --> 00:09:27.520
Who we are and how we exist
in a second to second,

00:09:27.520 --> 00:09:31.600
minute to minute temporal
and spatial existence.

00:09:31.600 --> 00:09:34.480
For example,
I am seated in a chair,

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:38.240
I am looking at a camera,
I am processing your words,

00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:41.600
those words mean something to me
because they are said

00:09:41.600 --> 00:09:44.656
in the English language
and so on and so forth.

00:09:44.656 --> 00:09:48.160
That is where my cortex comes in,
the higher functions come in.

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:51.600
But all of this I am doing
without having to think

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:55.040
about my heart rate,
my respiration, so on and so forth.

00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:58.720
So my state of being
literally at this point in time

00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:02.080
is a function of the limbic system
and that is allowing me

00:10:02.080 --> 00:10:07.360
not to overreact, to underreact,
to modulate my responses,

00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:11.600
not be fearful,
keep my memories kick into place,

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:16.880
and manage millions 
of processes happening

00:10:16.880 --> 00:10:19.760
without me even being aware of them.

00:10:19.760 --> 00:10:22.560
That in essence is your limbic system.

00:10:22.560 --> 00:10:29.440
Therefore, this system
is so critical to our functioning,

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:34.160
it comprises various parts
but these all talk to each other

00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:37.120
which is why we said
if we just look at them

00:10:37.120 --> 00:10:39.760
as individual components,
so here is the thalamus,

00:10:39.760 --> 00:10:42.160
here is the hypothalamus,
here is the amygdala,

00:10:42.160 --> 00:10:47.040
here is the anterior cingulate gyrus,
that doesn't help us to understand it.

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:53.040
So modern neuroscience,
although it still adopts this breaking

00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:56.480
into its component
parts approach,

00:10:56.480 --> 00:11:00.720
it still requires from
a neurological perspective

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:05.440
but also from a spiritual perspective
to understand how the whole thing

00:11:05.440 --> 00:11:12.240
works beautifully in sync
to come up with the final result

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:15.660
that is us functioning human beings.

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:19.920
This structure
of the brain,

00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:22.560
how does it align
with the interpretations

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:24.960
or teachings of Sahaj?

00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:28.000
So beautiful,
that's a great question Monika.

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:34.320
So the teachings of Shri Mataji
relate to realization

00:11:34.320 --> 00:11:38.720
or self-realization
to be very precise of an individual,

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:43.760
of what that true self is,
what is the ultimate reality

00:11:43.760 --> 00:11:46.960
of one's own existence,
one's own being

00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:52.000
and this particular aspect
is physiologically possible

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:54.960
and we'll deal with this
maybe a little later

00:11:54.960 --> 00:11:58.640
but how it aligns with
the teachings of Shri Mataji

00:11:58.640 --> 00:12:03.360
is that the entirety
of our spiritual system

00:12:03.360 --> 00:12:07.440
as we have said repeatedly
is one integrated function

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:12.960
and it is through this limbic system
or at the level of the limbic system

00:12:12.960 --> 00:12:15.200
is where it all comes together.

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:21.200
Our actions and our emotions,
our behaviors and our responses,

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:28.560
our processing of what is around us,
our upbringing, our conditionings,

00:12:28.560 --> 00:12:34.640
our affiliations, social, cultural,
so called religious, political,

00:12:34.640 --> 00:12:37.520
everything comes together
and is processed

00:12:37.520 --> 00:12:41.040
at the limbic system level
and of course with the help

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:44.800
of the higher centers
which is what allows us to do it

00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:47.680
but that is where it all
comes together vis-a-vis

00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:50.080
the alignment with
Shri Mataji's teaching

00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:56.640
so that we are one
integrated holistic being

00:12:56.640 --> 00:13:02.480
rather than just
a mere sum of our components.

00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:06.400
So from the first energy center
with its quality of innocence,

00:13:06.400 --> 00:13:09.520
the second energy center
with its quality

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:12.320
of pure knowledge,
third energy center

00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:17.040
with its qualities
of maintaining boundaries

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:20.080
or mariadas or dharma
as the expression goes

00:13:20.080 --> 00:13:23.280
in the Sanskrit language
from the sense of security

00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:27.520
and love and compassion
to the feeling of collective consciousness

00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:31.920
to feeling relaxed
about yourself and others,

00:13:31.920 --> 00:13:33.840
having a forgiving disposition.

00:13:33.840 --> 00:13:38.240
All these energy centers
that have those qualities

00:13:38.240 --> 00:13:44.000
are ultimately made possible
or manifest

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:47.280
because of the limbic system,
because of the amygdala,

00:13:47.280 --> 00:13:50.160
because of the thalamus,
because of the hypothalamus,

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:53.840
because of the other components
that we have not touched upon

00:13:53.840 --> 00:13:55.440
within the limbic system.

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:59.760
So the limbic system allows us

00:13:59.760 --> 00:14:03.840
to manifest the qualities
of the energy centers

00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:07.360
through this magnificent
evolutionary process

00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:10.080
that has brought us
to this ultimate step

00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:13.440
which is a breakthrough
in our consciousness

00:14:13.440 --> 00:14:15.520
through self-realization.

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:16.960
Does that help?

00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:19.120
Definitely it's a breakthrough
in the consciousness

00:14:19.120 --> 00:14:20.400
with the way
that you have explained

00:14:20.400 --> 00:14:24.560
and I think it was a very nice recap
of all the previous topics

00:14:24.560 --> 00:14:28.000
that you have covered in this series
about the different energy centers

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.880
and for those of you who have
missed those episodes

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:33.760
we would encourage you
to go back and watch them

00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:39.520
and this being the final episode
it just brings me to the next question

00:14:39.520 --> 00:14:42.000
about something that you
just mentioned towards the end

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:44.720
of your previous response
about the consciousness.

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:48.480
What is human consciousness
and can it be influenced

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:51.680
through internal or external means
and how does it relate

00:14:51.680 --> 00:14:53.520
to collective consciousness?

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:58.960
So that's a very profound question,

00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:02.320
so thanks for asking first of all.

00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:08.000
Second I would like to state
very very clearly

00:15:09.040 --> 00:15:13.440
one has to approach this
with a very healthy dose of humility.

00:15:13.440 --> 00:15:17.920
Not that the previous things
do not require humility

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:22.160
but this one even more so
if ever there was a need

00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:27.680
and the reason is that we still
do not know from a neurology perspective

00:15:27.680 --> 00:15:33.360
although an enormous amount of effort
has been expended on it.

00:15:33.360 --> 00:15:37.040
Consciousness remains
the final frontier

00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:41.320
and what is consciousness
as a function of neural correlates

00:15:41.320 --> 00:15:43.040
of our activity.

00:15:43.040 --> 00:15:48.640
In other words if an individual
is subjected to an imaging modality

00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:52.480
such as positron emission tomography
or PET scanning

00:15:52.480 --> 00:15:56.480
and you see what parts
of the brain are activated

00:15:56.480 --> 00:16:01.440
as individuals are put through
various different emotions

00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:06.400
is one way to understand
consciousness.

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:10.960
Consciousness implies two things.

00:16:10.960 --> 00:16:16.320
One is internal consciousness
and the other one is external consciousness.

00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:18.080
So there is a duality there.

00:16:18.080 --> 00:16:20.080
What do we mean
by internal consciousness?

00:16:20.080 --> 00:16:24.320
Internal consciousness is about
who I am, what I am feeling,

00:16:24.320 --> 00:16:29.520
where I am and my position
in the universe around me.

00:16:29.520 --> 00:16:33.760
External consciousness is everything
that is external to me.

00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:39.520
So there is a clear dividing line

00:16:39.520 --> 00:16:42.960
that I know or I perceive
or I am aware of

00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:49.040
whichever word applies
to what is self and what is non-self.

00:16:49.040 --> 00:16:53.840
What is within me that relates to me
and something that does not relate to me.

00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:58.960
It affects me but is not me
like for example this camera is not me

00:16:58.960 --> 00:17:02.080
but it is affecting me
because it is recording me.

